This paper proposes a novel convolutional neural network architecture for estimating geospatial functions using both overhead and ground-level images. This involves combining features extracted from both types of images and converting them into a dense feature map using kernel regression and density estimation. The output is a pixel-level labeling of the overhead image. This work involves computer vision (CV) techniques such as convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and machine learning (ML) techniques such as kernel regression and density estimation.
